content.description: Down Wild Cove Road tucked away in the forest are a series of limestone boulders which host a good many climbs, possibly 30 or more lines exist. These boulders lay at the base of the scree field just downhill of the large overhang on Wrickled Rock. The boulders get a good bit of sun, and are mostly good quality rock, though some cleaning wouldn't hurt. Boulders are 12-20 plus feet with vert, slab, steep, and roof sections. Id guess grades could be had from V0-V8or 9. I will update with further info after more exploration.
